Commentary Text: Ish Sodhi to Williamson, out Caught by Buttler!! Huge wicket! Maiden IPL wicket for Sodhi! And it's his NZ skipper that he has sent back. Vital breakthrough for RR because the SRH captain was batting like a dream. This one shot through low shockingly from a good length as Williamson tried to play the cut from the crease. It was a great take from Buttler and S.Ravi felt there was a bottom edge. KW didn't and went for the review. The replays didn't show anything to be honest but the snicko has a different story to tell. Tiniest of spikes or murmurs to be precise and Williamson had to go. Williamson c Buttler b Ish Sodhi 63(43) [4s-7 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Gowtham to Hales, out Caught by Samson!! Gowtham has another! He's bowled exceptionally well today and has started this spell with a bang as well. Hales was moving around the crease and Gowtham smartly dragged this wider outside off. Asked the Englishman to fetch it and he could only slice it high in the air. Easiest of catches for Samson at backward point. Decent start to the IPL for Hales but he would have wanted to kick on and make a really big one. Timely strike for RR because this partnership was starting to open up. Hales c Samson b Gowtham 45(39) [4s-4]

Commentary Text: Jofra Archer to Williamson, no run, oopsy. Edged and Tripathi puts down an absolute sitter at first slip. Mind you, this is the second spill for him in the tournament at that position. He dropped one off Watson at Pune and the Australian ended up scoring a ton. How costly is it going to be today? We will have to wait and see. On a back of a length and it shot up to trouble Williamson, who poked at it half-heartedly. Went straight to Tripathi, who got both hands but shelled it. Archer is disappointed

Commentary Text: Gowtham to Dhawan, out Bowled!! Bowled 'em. Gowtham sends Dhawan packing back to the hut. Very, very poor shot from the southpaw. Totally misjudged the length there. It was rifled quick outside off, the ball was skidding off the pitch. Dhawan with his knee bent first tried to sweep and then as an afterthought tried to open his bat face to guide it past the solitary slip. But the ball just fizzed off the deck, took his inside edge and deflected back onto the stumps. Gowtham breaks into a celebratory jig. Just the wicket RR wanted, the dangerous Dhawan back to the hut early. Dhawan b Gowtham 6(4) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Y Pathan to Stokes, out Bowled!! My word. He's brought on as a roller, to sneak an over under the radar, but such is the power that practically anybody in a Hyderabadi jersey can pick wickets. Pathan holds the ball back in his palm as he fires in a slider. Yes it was short, but certainly not for Stokes to rock back as deep as he did in trying to heave it away. Misses big time, sneaking under the bat. Well under. And yeah, off's uprooted. Stokes b Y Pathan 0(3)

Commentary Text: S Kaul to Samson, out Caught by Hales!! Times his way to Hales. He just can't look ugly, and the overdose of timing he's got in him isn't quite on par with the fields put out.
